      "question": "In the given figure, $PA$ and $PB$ are tangents to a circle with centre $O$ from an external point $P$. If $\\angle APB = 60^\\circ$ and the radius of the circle is $6$ cm, find the length of the chord $AB$.",
      "answer": "$6\\sqrt{3}$ cm",
      "solution": {
        "steps": [
          "Identify that in $\\triangle PAB$, $PA = PB$ as tangents from an external point are equal. Since $\\angle APB = 60^\\circ$, $\\triangle PAB$ is an equilateral triangle, so $AB = PA = PB$.",
          "In $\\triangle OAP$, $\\angle OAP = 90^\\circ$ (radius is perpendicular to tangent). Since $OP$ bisects $\\angle APB$, $\\angle OPA = 30^\\circ$.",
          "Use trigonometry in $\\triangle OAP$ to find $PA$: $\\tan(30^\\circ) = \\frac{OA}{PA} \\Rightarrow \\frac{1}{\\sqrt{3}} = \\frac{6}{PA} \\Rightarrow PA = 6\\sqrt{3}$ cm.",
          "Conclude that $AB = PA = 6\\sqrt{3}$ cm."
        ],
        "derivation": "$PA = PB \\text{ and } \\angle APB = 60^\\circ \\Rightarrow \\triangle PAB \\text{ is equilateral } \\Rightarrow AB = PA \\\\ \\text{In } \\triangle OAP, \\angle OAP = 90^\\circ, \\angle OPA = \\frac{1}{2} \\angle APB = 30^\\circ \\\\ \\tan(30^\\circ) = \\frac{OA}{PA} \\Rightarrow \\frac{1}{\\sqrt{3}} = \\frac{6}{PA} \\\\ PA = 6\\sqrt{3} \\text{ cm} \\\\ AB = 6\\sqrt{3} \\text{ cm}$"
      },
